io.dazraf.vertx.futures.processors

Interface CallProcessor<T,R>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Function<io.vertx.core.Future<T>,io.vertx.core.Future<R>>, FutureProcessor<T,R>

    public interface CallProcessor<T,R>
extends FutureProcessor<T,R>
    Functions for creating call processor. The semantics of call is to pass the state of the chain (of type T) to a function that returns a Future of type R

        static <InputCollection extends Collection<T>,T,R> CallProcessor<InputCollection,List<R>> flatMap(Function<T,io.vertx.core.Future<R>> flatMapFunction)
        Given a succesfully resolved chain, producing List<T>, receive the result and pass each element to the function flatMapFunction which in turn returns a Future<R>. The resulting List<Future<R>> is transformed and returned as Future<List<R>>

        R - the type of result returned by callFunction

        Returns:
        the processor
